The paper deals with the maximum independent set problem on graphs, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The techniques used in the paper involve Lovasz theta function, semidefinite programming, and Ramsey theory, which are all topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves the study of graph structures and properties, which falls under computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses approximation algorithms and hardness results, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
